l":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%AA%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"house, building"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tent (dwelling)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"room, apartment, flat"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"commercial house"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"settlement, decision, scheme"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"garden bed"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"family, dynasty"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"box, case, covering, sheath"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verse, couplet, distich"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to brood"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to contrive, to hatch (a plan, plot)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put (someone) up for the night"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to flunk, to fail (in school)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *bayt-. Cognate with Amharic ቤት (bēt)."},"ipa":["/bajt/","/baj.ja.ta/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3602","headword_ar":"بَيْتٌ","root":"byt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"properly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having more than one pole;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but often applied without this restriction: and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a house; a chamber; an apartment; a closet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayot","text_ar":"بَيْت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats'"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEar","text_ar":"شَعَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (M, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wool:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of hair"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair-cloth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is that kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which has more than one pole:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the word is masc.: and applies to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) tents of goats' hair are peculiar to people of cold countries and of fertile regions, where the goats have abundant hair; for the goats of the Arabs of the desert have short hair, not long enough to be spun: (T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":":) a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibaA='","text_ar":"خِبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a small"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"of wool or of hair: a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is larger than a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xbA='","text_ar":"خبا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": next is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miZal~ap","text_ar":"مِظَلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is larger than the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mZl~p","text_ar":"مظلّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it is large and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muraw~aq","text_ar":"مُرَوَّق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"furnished with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riwaAq","text_ar":"رِوَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]: (T:) Ibn-El-Kelbee says that the Arabs have six kinds of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"; namely, a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qub~ap","text_ar":"قُبَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is of skins, or tanned hides; a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miZal~ap","text_ar":"مِظَلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", of hair; a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibaA='","text_ar":"خِبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", of wool; a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bijaAd","text_ar":"بِجَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":", of soft hair ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabar","text_ar":"وَبَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"); a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayomap","text_ar":"خَيْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", of trees; an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uqonap","text_ar":"اُقْنَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", of stone; and a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawoT","text_ar":"سَوْط"},{"kind":"text","text":", of hair; or this is the smallest of them: El-Baghdádee says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xbA'","text_ar":"خباء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"made of soft hair ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabar","text_ar":"وَبَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"), or of wool, or of hair [commonly so called] ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEar","text_ar":"شَعَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"), upon two poles, or three; and that a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon six poles, or more, to the number of nine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Towsheeh it is said that the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xbA'","text_ar":"خباء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"of any kind: (TA:) a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a structure"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of clay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tough or cohesive clay or earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K;) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of baked bricks;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of stone;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the name being likewise applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a structure of a kind other than the structures which are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axobiyap","text_ar":"اَخْبِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tents"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M;) signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a habitation"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of any kind; an abode; a dwelling"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArN","text_ar":"دَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) [and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a chamber;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single roofed structure"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Kull)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a place of entrance;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manozilN","text_ar":"مَنْزِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being applied to what comprises more than one [such]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":", and a roofed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHon","text_ar":"صَحْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or vacant part, and a kitchen, inhabited by a man with his family]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArN","text_ar":"دَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", that which comprises more than one [such]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"and more than one [such]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manozil","text_ar":"مَنْزِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"and a [court, or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHon","text_ar":"صَحْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"without a roof: (Kull:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyuwtN","text_ar":"بُيُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K, &c.,) also pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biyuwtN","text_ar":"بِيُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboyaAtN","text_ar":"اَبْيَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) the latter a pl. of pauc.; (TA;) and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyuwtaAtN","text_ar":"بُيُوتَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaAyiytu","text_ar":"اَبَايِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboyaAwaAtN","text_ar":"اَبْيَاوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, M, K,) which last is extr.: (M:) the dim. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyayotN","text_ar":"بُيَيْتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also pronounced ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biyayotN","text_ar":"بِيَيْتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and the vulgar say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buwayotN","text_ar":"بُوَيْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) which is not allowable. (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa jaAriY","text_ar":"هُوَ جَارِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayota bayota","text_ar":"بَيْتَ بَيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is my neighbour"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent to tent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house to house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by contiguity"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of our habitations"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt byt","text_ar":"بيت بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"being made indecl. with fet-h for the termination because they are two nouns made one: (S:) Sb says that some of the Arabs make them [thus] indecl., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xamosapa","text_ar":"خَمْسَةَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$ara","text_ar":"عَشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and some make the former a prefixed noun governing the latter in the gen. case, [saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayota bayotK","text_ar":"بَيْتَ بَيْتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] except when used as a denotative of state: (M:) one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotFA libayotK","text_ar":"بَيْتًا لِبَيْتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotN","text_ar":"بَيْتٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libayotK","text_ar":"لِبَيْتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Fr, T;) which last, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotN A_ilaY bayotK","text_ar":"بَيْتٌ اـِلَى بَيْتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is the original form. (Har p. 353.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaY fulaAnN EalaY","text_ar":"بَنَى فُلَانٌ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@moraA^atihi","text_ar":"ا@مْرَاَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one constructed a tent over his wife,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one had his wife conducted to him on the occasion of his marriage, and brought her,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had her brought, into a pitched tent, having conveyed thither the utensils and furniture and other things that they required."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu","text_ar":"اَهْلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotu Aln~abiY~i","text_ar":"بَيْتُ النَّبِىِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people of the house of the Prophet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Prophet's wives and his daughter and 'Alee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ahola A@lobayoti","text_ar":"اَهْلَ ا@لْبَيْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxuS~u A^ahola Albayoti","text_ar":"يَخُصُّ اَهْلَ البَيْتِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He means particularly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"peculiarly, the people of the house"},{"kind":"text","text":"], in the Kur xxxiii. 33:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw","text_ar":"بَنُو"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEo$ar","text_ar":"مَعْشَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ahol","text_ar":"اَهْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=l","text_ar":"ا=ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", as prefixed nouns, being, as Sb says, the nouns most frequently occurring in the accus. case [for the reason indicated above, or, as the Arabian grammarians express it,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAixotiSaASi","text_ar":"الاِخْتِصَاصِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b2-  It also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pavilion, palace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mansion, such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSor","text_ar":"قَصْر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, K:) whence the saying of Gabriel,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ba$~iro xadiyjapa","text_ar":"بَشِّرْ خَدِيجَةَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bibayotK mino qaSabK","text_ar":"بِبَيْتٍ مِنْ قَصَبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rejoice thou Khadeejeh by the announcement of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pavilion"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qSr","text_ar":"قصر"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of hollow pearls,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of emerald."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qSb","text_ar":"قصب"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyuwtFA gayora masokuwnapK","text_ar":"بُيُوتًا غَيْرَ مَسْكُونَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Uninhabited houses"},{"kind":"text","text":"], in the Kur xxiv. 29, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"buildings for the reception of travellers, or for merchants and their goods, and the shops of the merchants and places in which things are sold, the entering of which is allowed by their owners:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ruins which a man enters for the purpose of easing nature."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyuwt","text_ar":"بُيُوت"},{"kind":"text","text":"which God has permitted to be raised, mentioned in the same chapter, verse 36, are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mosques,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"places of worship:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to El-Hasan,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Jerusalem"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotu Almaqodisi","text_ar":"بَيْتُ المَقْدِسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"); the pl. being applied to it as a mark of honour. (Zj, M.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albayotu","text_ar":"البَيْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The House"},{"kind":"text","text":"] applies particularly to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Kaabeh"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Mekkeh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"بَيْتُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the House of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (AAF, M;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albayotu","text_ar":"البَيْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaraAmu","text_ar":"الحَرَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Sacred House"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albayotu","text_ar":"البَيْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEatiyqu","text_ar":"العَتِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Ancient House"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S and K &c. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Etq","text_ar":"عتق"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albayotu AlmaEomuwru","text_ar":"البَيْتُ المَعْمُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (Bd in lii. 4.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotu AlmaAli","text_ar":"بَيْتُ المَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The treasury of the state."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotu AlmaA='i","text_ar":"بَيْتُ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a euphemism for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The privy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because water is put there for the purpose of ablution: also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotu AlfaraAgi","text_ar":"بَيْتُ الفَرَاغِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.] ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ark"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Noah: so in the Kur lxxi. last verse. (T.) ―         -b4-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A grave;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, IAth, K;) app. by way of comparison. (M.) So in a trad. of Aboo-Dharr:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayofa taSonaEu A_i*aA maAta Aln~aAsu Hat~aY","text_ar":"كَيْفَ تَصْنَعُ اـِذَا مَاتَ النَّاسُ حَتَّى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakuwnu Albayotu biAlwaSiyfi","text_ar":"يَكُونُ البَيْتُ بِالوَصِيفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How will thou do when men shall die so that the grave shall be sold for the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"servant-"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boy?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth.) ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"habitation"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"surofap","text_ar":"سُرْفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", which it constructs in a beautiful manner, (A'Obeyd, M,) of fragments of sticks; (Yaakoob, M;) and of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SayodanaAniY~","text_ar":"صَيْدَنَانِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which it makes in the interior of the earth, and covers over: (A'Obeyd, M:) and (assumed tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hole,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~","text_ar":"ضَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: and (assumed tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"web"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the spider: all, app., as being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayot","text_ar":"بَيْت"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man. (M.) ―         -b6-  (tropical:)  A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"household."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) ―         -b7-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, IAar, T, M, A) of a man. (M, A.) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^akibarN gay~araniY A^mo bayotu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hath old age altered me, or a wife?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (As, T:) or here it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a household."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b8-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Arabs; (T, Msb, K; *) as when one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotu tamiymK fiY baniY HanoZalapa","text_ar":"بَيْتُ تَمِيمٍ فِى بَنِى حَنْظَلَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The nobility of Temeem is in the sons of Handhaleh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T, Msb: *) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"family that comprises the nobility of a tribe;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=lu HiSonK","text_ar":"ا=لُ حِصْنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fazaAriy~uwn","text_ar":"فَزَارِيُّون"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=lu Aljud~ayoni","text_ar":"ا=لُ الجُدَّيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ayobaAniy~uwn","text_ar":"شَيْبَانِيُّون"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=lu Eabodi AlmadaAni","text_ar":"ا=لُ عَبْدِ المَدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAriviy~uwn","text_ar":"حَارِثِيُّون"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which three were asserted by Ibn-El-Kelbee to be the highest of the families thus called of the Arabs: (M:) [see a verse of El-Lahabee cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyuwtN","text_ar":"بُيُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyuwtaAtN","text_ar":"بُيُوتَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M,) the latter being pl. of the former. (T.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa mino A^aholi AlbuyuwtaAti","text_ar":"هُوَ مِنْ اَهْلِ البُيُوتَاتِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is of the people of nobility:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino bayotK kariymK","text_ar":"مِنْ بَيْتٍ كَرِيمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a generous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble, house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"family"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaY","text_ar":"بَنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A noble person:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyuwtN","text_ar":"بُيُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyuwtaAtN","text_ar":"بُيُوتَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN bayotu qawomihi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ بَيْتُ قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the noble person of his people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l-'Omeythil El-Aarabee, M.) ―         -b10-  (tropical:)  The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"furniture termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faro$","text_ar":"فَرْش"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Mgh, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mataAE","text_ar":"مَتَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is sufficient for a tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazaw~ajotu fulaAnapa EalaY bayotK","text_ar":"تَزَوَّجْتُ فُلَانَةَ عَلَى بَيْتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I married,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took as a wife, such a woman for"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my giving"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"furniture sufficient for a tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"furniture of a house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) [See 1, last sentence.] ―         -b11-  A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayot","text_ar":"بَيْت"},{"kind":"text","text":"of poetry, (T, S, M, Msb,) or of the poet, (K,) is (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A verse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what consists of certain known divisions"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feet"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajozaA='u Alt~afoEiyli","text_ar":"اَجْزَا=ءُ التَّفْعِيلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; being termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"metaphorically, because of the conjoining of its component parts, one to another, in a particular manner, like as those of a tent are conjoined in its construction; (Msb;) because it consists of words collected together in a regular manner, and so resembles a tent, which is composed of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqof","text_ar":"سَقْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kifaA='","text_ar":"كِفَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riwaAq","text_ar":"رِوَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eumud","text_ar":"عُمُد"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) it is derived from the same word signifying a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibaA='","text_ar":"خِبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or tent], and applies to the small and the great, as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaz","text_ar":"رَجَز"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tawiyl","text_ar":"طَوِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and is [said to be] thus called because it comprises words like as the tent comprises its inhabitants; wherefore its component parts are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobaAb","text_ar":"اَسْبَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awotaAd","text_ar":"اَوْتَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":", as being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsbAb","text_ar":"اسباب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AwtAd","text_ar":"اوتاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"of tents: (M:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboyaAtN","text_ar":"اَبْيَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyuwtN","text_ar":"بُيُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, Msb,) the latter mentioned by Sb and IJ, (M,) [but rare,] and [pl. pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaAyiytu","text_ar":"اَبَايِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) Abu-l-Hasan says that if the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"of poetry be likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is a tent or other kind of structure, there is no reason why it should not have the same pl. forms as the latter has. (L.) By the following words of a poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wabayotK EalaY Zahori AlmaTiY~i banayotuhu\n                      \n                     \n                        biA^asomara ma$oquwqi AlxayaA$iymi yaroEufu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Many a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the back of the camel have I"},{"kind":"page_break","n":281},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constructed with a lawny thing slit in the nose"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bleeding"},{"kind":"text","text":"], is meant, many a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"of poetry have I written with the reed-pen. (S.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albayota","text_ar":"البَيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", written after a quotation of a part of a verse of poetry, means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiqoraA^i Albayota","text_ar":"اِقْرَاِ البَيْتَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Read thou the verse."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotu AlqaSiydapi","text_ar":"بَيْتُ القَصِيدَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"text","text":"chief"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"verse of the poem"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a phrase employed when a person composes a poem in praise of any one from whom he would obtain some object of desire and want, being applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that verse of the poem in which the author's want is mentioned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is a proverbial expression relating to that which is extraordinary and strange, and used in denoting the superiority of a part of a thing over the whole of it [regarded as a whole]: [hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN A^aw~alu Aljariydapi wabayotu AlqaSiydapi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ اَوَّلُ الجَرِيدَةِ وَبَيْتُ القَصِيدَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the first of the detachment of horsemen, and the chief verse of the poem"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har p. 441.)"}],"source_refs":["M","A","Mgh","Msb","K","T","TA","Kull","S","Sb","Fr","As","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n3603","headword_ar":"بِيتٌ","root":"byt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biytapN","text_ar":"بِيتَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}